mainEntity.name: How long does ceramic coating last?

acceptedAnswer.text: Our ceramic coatings last between 2-5 years depending on the package you choose. Our 2-year coating provides excellent protection at an affordable price point, while our 5-year graphene-infused ceramic coating offers maximum durability and enhanced hydrophobic properties. Proper maintenance can extend the life of any ceramic coating.

mainEntity.name: How much does ceramic coating cost in Los Angeles?

acceptedAnswer.text: Our ceramic coating services start at $450 for our 2-Year coating on a standard sedan. Our premium 5-Year Graphene Coating starts at $999. Pricing varies based on vehicle size, condition, and the amount of paint correction needed before coating. We provide exact quotes after inspecting your vehicle.

mainEntity.name: Is ceramic coating worth the investment?

acceptedAnswer.text: Yes, ceramic coating is worth the investment for several reasons: 1) It provides years of protection versus months from traditional wax, 2) It maintains your vehicle's appearance and value over time, 3) It makes maintenance easier with its hydrophobic properties, and 4) It provides superior protection against environmental damage. For vehicles you plan to keep for several years, ceramic coating offers excellent value.

mainEntity.name: Do you come to my location to apply ceramic coating?

acceptedAnswer.text: Yes! As a mobile ceramic coating service in Los Angeles, we bring our professional-grade products and equipment directly to your home or office throughout Los Angeles and Orange County. We require a garage or covered area for the application process to ensure proper curing and dust-free application.
